==English==

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|en|neutral|on}}. {{coin|en|William Sutherland|w=William Sutherland (physicist)|nat=Scottish-Australian|occ=physicist|in=1899|nobycat=1}} in a paper in the ''{{w|Philosophical Magazine}}''. Subsequent usage was sporadic and theoretical, sometimes referring to [[neutrino]]s rather than neutrons, and the modern sense was reintroduced alongside {{m|en|proton}} by {{w|Ernest Rutherford}} in 1920.

